cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper is about developing a new metric to evaluate dialogue quality in a domain-independent manner. It involves creating a new annotation scheme and experimenting with machine learning models to estimate user satisfaction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the paper involves developing models to estimate user satisfaction and improving dialogue management.
